      • Serialization Methods

        • readObject

          private void readObject(java.io.ObjectInputStream in)
                 throws java.io.IOException,
                        java.lang.ClassNotFoundException
          Read an object from an input stream, de-serializing it. This custom de-serialization method calls the default read-object method to read in all non-transient fields. This method has the public access class because subclasses AND proxies need to call it from their own readObject() methods.
          Throws:
          java.lang.ClassNotFoundException - when a nested object class can't be found
          java.io.IOException - when there is an IO problem reading the stream

      • Serialization Methods

        • readObject

          private void readObject(java.io.ObjectInputStream in)
                 throws java.io.IOException,
                        java.lang.ClassNotFoundException
          Read an object from an input stream, de-serializing it. This custom de-serialization method calls the default read-object method to read in all non-transient fields then runs a series of setters in the readObjectSetters list to de-serialize any transient elements.
          Throws:
          java.lang.ClassNotFoundException - when a nested object class can't be found
          java.io.IOException - when there is an IO problem reading the stream
